Kopitiam - modular incremental interactive full functional static verification of Java code

Information about this project can be found:
* NFM2011 paper http://www.itu.dk/~hame/nfm2011.pdf
* Design http://www.itu.dk/~hame/kopitiam-design.pdf
* update-site (for eclipse) http://www.itu.dk/~hame/kopitiam/
* On 64 Bit -Xint has to be passed to eclipse (disable just-in-time compilation)

Prerequisites:
* Eclipse SDK (from http://download.eclipse.org/eclipse/downloads/) tested is 3.6
* Scala IDE (from http://www.scala-ide.org/) tested is Scala IDE 2.0.0-beta4 with Scala 2.9.0.final
* runtime: Coq (from http://coq.inria.fr/download) tested is 8.3pl1

Setup:
1) checkout git repository
2) eclipse -> File -> Import -> Existing Projects into Workspace -> root == git checkout -> uncheck 'copy projects into workspace'
3) Build project (takes some time, especially at 4%)
4) Run Configurations -> Plug-ins -> Workspace -> Kopitiam -> Auto-start == true
5) Run

Useful links
http://www.assembla.com/wiki/show/scala-ide/Eclipse_Plugin_Development_using_the_Scala_IDE (especially deployment: check "use class files from workspace"!)
